th high walls, gates, and bars, besides a large number of rural villages. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:3:6","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"We completely destroyed them, as we had done to King Sihon of Heshbon, destroying the men, women, and children of every city. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:3:7","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"But we took all the livestock and the spoil from the cities as plunder for ourselves. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Nm 21:32","book":"Num","chapter":21,"verse":32,"letter":"a"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Nm 21:32","book":"Num","chapter":21,"verse":32}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:3:8","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“At that time we took the land from the two Amorite kings across the Jordan, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 50:10–11","book":"Gen","chapter":50,"verse":10,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 1:1","book":"Deu","chapter":1,"verse":1,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 1:5","book":"Deu","chapter":1,"verse":5,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jos 1:14–15","book":"Jos","chapter":1,"verse":14,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" from the Arnon Valley as far as Mount Hermon, "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 50:10–11","book":"Gen","chapter":50,"verse":10},{"label":"Dt 1:1","book":"Deu","chapter":1,"verse":1},{"label":"Dt 1:5","book":"Deu","chapter":1,"verse":5},{"label":"Jos 1:14–15","book":"Jos","chapter":1,"verse":14}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:3:9","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"which the Sidonians call Sirion, but the Amorites call Senir, "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:3:10","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"all the cities of the plateau, Gilead, and Bashan as far as Salecah and Edrei, cities of Og’s kingdom in Bashan. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jos 13:11","book":"Jos","chapter":13,"verse":11,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],